McDonald's hamburgers, fries and golden

However, many Chinese, who earn an average $32 a month, are still unable to afford fancy meals at restaurants.
At the restaurant, a Big Mac costs $1.14, a bag of fries 48 cents and a shake 74 cents.
The 500-seat McDonald's restaurant in a three-story building is operated by McDonald's Restaurant Shenzhen Ltd., a wholly owned subsidiary of McDonald's Hong Kong.
It is managed by a Chinese national, Chen Tikang, and his son, Chen Yin, who is the restaurant manager.
He is an assistant manager at the restaurant.
